HEADWORD: Repression
<hw>Re*pres"sion</hw> <pr>(r?-pr?sh"?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧pression</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of repressing, or state of being repressed;
<as>as, the <ex>repression</ex> of evil and evil doers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which represses; check; restraint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repressive</ent>⟦br⟧
